    • getPayMultiplier

      public static int getPayMultiplier​(ThreeString thePull)
      "getPayMultiplier() takes the pullString as a parameter, and inspects it to determine what its pay multiplier should be: 5? 15? 100? 0? It does this by looking at the three strings inside the passed-in ThreeString object and using if statements to determine and return the right value. The method will return one of the values; 0, 5, 15, 30, 50 or 100."

    • display

      public static void display​(ThreeString thePull, int winnings)

    • main

      public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
      main() will have a loop that is controlled by a value returned from getBet(). As long as that value is non-zero, we keep playing. Each time through the loop, we have to call pull() to get the pullString as a return value. Then we need to pass that to getPayMultiplier() to find the multiplier. We then compute the winnings based on the previous information, and finally we display it all using display(). When the user wants to quit, call toStringWinnings() and print the returned string.
